translated: Holmgren, Gustaf Fredrik, lawyer, Gothenburg, born February 22, 1880 in Kungsbacka to bank cashier Gustaf H. and Malin Schöld-ström. Married in 1907 to Milly Oedegaard. Children: Hillevi, born in 1908, died in 1938; Per Gustaf, born in 1909, film director in Stockholm; Harriet, born in 1911, married to department manager Bertil Lundberg in Gothenburg. Completed his law degree at Lund University in 1899, pre-law degree in 1901, and passed the Court of Appeals exam in 1904. Became a trainee notary in Göta Court of Appeals in 1904, served as a probationary judge in Fjäre and Viske Courts in 1906, was employed by the law firm Almstrand & Wennerberg in Gothenburg in 1906, became a partner in 1912, and had his own law practice in Gothenburg. Also worked at the Riksbanken (Swedish Central Bank) branch in Gothenburg as a clerk and representative from 1912 to 1917, served as representative for Gbgs Handelsbank (Gothenburg Commercial Bank) and was a board member and chairman for A-B Gbgssystemet (Gothenburg System Companies). Also served as representative and member of the executive committee for Västsv:es Allm. Rest. A-B, Konsortium Kampsax, A-B Fören. Piano- & Orgellfabr., and other companies. Served as a member of the board for Nydqvist & Holm A-B and others. Became a member of the Swedish Bar Association in 1908 and continues to be a member to this day. Has been awarded the Royal Order of the North Star (RNO), Royal Order of Vasa (RVO), and Knight Second Class of the Order of the Polar Star (KDD02gr).
